🎶 @westermanmusic “blue comanche-sketch”

I meant to make this painting last spring, but life got wild and I had to take some space from my intimidating ambitions. don’t be fooled by her grace, she nearly broke me. I started over a couple of times. but day by day, week by week, month by month ::she materialized:: what a rollercoaster ride it can be sometimes, but always leading back to the never ending reminder to never give up on the vision because that is the womb phase of all artistic endeavors. even though I have chosen not to have children of my own, I have a profound fascination with this phase of motherhood. Not only is it one of the most beautiful forms to paint, with its taught and soft curves that perfectly reflect light like the moon; it’s also the truest form of, and union with Creation. everything I paint is a reflection of my truest spirit in its current form. reliving the womb experience, while impossible in its literal sense, feels like a metaphorical exploration. we all want to feel safe and secure, amirite? anyways, please share this image with any mother or mother to be. and dm me for inquiries because she’s available for purchase. 

WHEN SHE MADE THE WORLD
watercolor on 40ish x 30sh “ cotton rag paper
